THE WORLD 
Japanese Prime Minister Toshiki Kaifu flew to Ottawa after a two-day visit to 
Mexico City in which he pledged to work with Mexico to help solve economic and 
environmental problems. Kaifu offered financial and technological assistance to 
Mexico and said that Japan will cooperate in efforts to combat pollution in 
Mexico City. His visit to Canada will conclude a 12-day trip that began in the 
United States. 
